sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Cmd as Existing command entry point
    participant WF as Workflow orchestration
    participant Reg as Existing registry
    participant LC as Existing lifecycle
    participant Ren as Static renderer
    participant Lock as Workspace mutation lock
    participant T as Registered target
    participant Ev as Evidence
    participant Gate as DPA-500 gates

    User->>Cmd: request governed refresh
    Cmd->>WF: preserve existing command/workflow contract
    WF->>Reg: resolve registered projection contract
    Reg-->>WF: validated declarative contract
    WF->>LC: request dry-run plan
    LC->>Ren: render exactly one target
    Ren-->>LC: text or bytes only
    LC-->>WF: immutable plan + identity
    WF->>LC: execute exact plan
    LC->>Lock: acquire local mutation lock
    LC->>Reg: revalidate contract
    LC->>T: atomically replace complete file
    LC->>T: reread and verify bytes
    LC->>Ev: emit bounded record
    LC->>Lock: release
    LC-->>WF: written-unverified
    WF->>Gate: request acceptance evaluation
    Gate-->>WF: accepted or blocked

    Note over Cmd,T: For CURRENT_HANDOFF, adapt admin-refresh-pr; do not create a parallel DPA-only writer.
